</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallerus>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#333333>(11/19/02 4:46:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7907.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: It's pretty simple...</span><hr size=1> we always pull him into the house right before him.  The trip is pretty easy with a standard group (tank,cleric,chanter,mage, rogue, someone else) &amp; is pretty good xp to around 57 or so I think.  Be prepared to do it a lot - the torch seems to drop about 1 in 8-10 times or so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=niden>Niden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 364<br> <font color=#333333>(11/19/02 4:56:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7907.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   It's really easy.</span><hr size=1> A single group of 60's can do this in 15 minutes with ease.  A group of 55+ can do it with no trouble.<br>
<br>
You need a rogue to pick locks, a healer (clr/dru/shm), and a tank of some sort (war/pal/mnk/shd/whatever).  Fill the two other spots with whatever; melee damage is good, or a backup healer if you're short on dps, but it doesn't really matter.  Monks and SK's are particularly useful as they can FD if necessary when pulling.  Some sort of crowd control (brd/enc) is also useful.  Have the healer memorize a spell to cure blindness from the reavers, and have tanks make a &gt;&gt;&gt; BLIND &lt;&lt;&lt; hotkey or something.<br>
<br>
Zone in and run/train to the back of the zone.  Kill green mobs.  Have the rogue pick the door.  Kill green mobs, and kill the reaver. Proceed through the door in the back right of the room, and follow the hallway to the right.  Fight up the ramp until you come to the door at the end, but DO NOT OPEN IT.  If you do, you'll probably die.  Instead, there's a fake wall right next to it that opens out onto the invisible ramp.  Follow it up, and basically just fight up the skyway until you come to the end.  Neh'Ashiir's reaver is in the small building at the VERY, VERY end.<br>
<br>
Easiest strategy is to pull her out and fight her in the larger, second-to-last building immediately before hers.  She's non-aggro when she spawns, and she doesn't despawn immediately, so you have time to heal or med for a few seconds after killing her reaver(s).  She's a cleric/shaman hybrid type mob, and like reavers, is nearly completely MR.  Not difficult if you can kill reavers.  Torch is uncommon, but not really rare.  Common drop is the ORS.  Neh'Ashiir's reaver will respawn in around two hours, so if it doesn't drop the first time, you can head to seb and xp for 90 minutes and then come back.<br>
<br>
The critical part is to just stay in control.  It's easy to get overwhelmed by mobs if you don't stay together or if there's a bad pull, just like any other situation.  It's a total cakewalk with a group of decently geared 60's that have a remote clue what they're doing.<br>
